SIMPLE: triplet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triplet
<hw>Trip"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Triple</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A collection or combination of
three of a kind; three united.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Poetry)</fld> <def>Three verses rhyming
together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A group of three notes sung or
played in the tree of two.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Three children or offspring born at
one birth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triple-tail</ent>⟦br⟧
